ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">Still, even those who know Broccoli well were caught off guard by today=
=E2=80=99s news. She
dropped zero hints during November=E2=80=99s Governors Awards appearance. A=
 friend who saw her <em>this week</em> had no idea what was coming. So, wha=
t actually happened? I spoke to a couple of Bondworld people who speculated=
 that, with Wilson turning 83 and stepping away from the family business, B=
arbara was forced to contemplate a tougher and lonelier path on future film=
s. (The children of Broccoli and Wilson, especially <strong>Gregg Wilson</s=
trong>, have been involved in past Bond movies but were
not seen as stewards of the franchise=E2=80=94at least not yet.) And despit=
e all the speculation, there was nothing Bond-related in serious developmen=
t at Eon. Broccoli had met with actors, as she always does. But it=E2=80=99=
s nuts: Movies were pre-selling at festivals based on <strong>Aaron Taylor-=
Johnson</strong> being cast as the next Bond, but there was never any real =
movement with him=E2=80=94or any potential <strong>Daniel Craig</strong> su=
ccessor, for that matter.=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">In f=
act, one person who spoke to Barbara recently about Bond said she has been =
genuinely stumped about how to replace Craig after five creatively and fina=
ncially successful films together. Broccoli was even questioning how the ne=
xt iteration of the character should look and act. Not a sign of enthusiasm=
=2E</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bo=
ttom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:=
0;margin-bottom:0px;">Given all that, I think the most
likely scenario is that Amazon simply wore Broccoli down. She couldn=E2=80=
=99t work with them, and at some point she recognized that one of the world=
=E2=80=99s largest companies isn=E2=80=99t actually all that temporary. Nor=
 is the streaming revolution that Amazon represents, and that has challenge=
d the Broccolis=E2=80=99 model of making a single big-budget blockbuster ev=
ery few years=E2=80=94and keeping it away from home video for as long as po=
ssible. Bond has remained the rare thriving theatrical franchise, with the =
Covid-delayed
<em>No Time to Die </em>grossing nearly $800 million as theaters reopened i=
n late 2021. But for how long? Barbara could have tried to wait out the Ama=
zon bros, but that would have risked allowing the property to grow stale. S=
he could have tried to get Hopkins to partner with another studio with whom=
 she <em>could</em> work, which Amazon would probably never allow. Or she c=
ould get paid and walk away.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">And
let=E2=80=99s be clear: She <em>is</em> walking away. The deal is a joint v=
enture, and I=E2=80=99m told the family will be credited and paid each time=
 a piece of Bond content=E2=80=94c-word intentional=E2=80=94is released. Bu=
t Broccoli and Wilson are out as hands-on producers. It=E2=80=99s not quite=
 <strong>George Lucas</strong> selling <em>Star Wars</em> to Disney for $4 =
billion and disappearing, but the Lucas deal is probably the closest analog=
 here (though Lucasfilm came with other assets, like <em>Indiana Jones </em=
>and the ILM
visual effects unit). It ends family control of a major entertainment prope=
rty, and further chips away at traditional Hollywood players in favor of th=
e Big Tech overlords that increasingly dominate media and entertainment. Gr=
eat work, everyone.<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">B=
roccoli has other endeavors, of course, including theater projects and a re=
make of Fleming=E2=80=99s <em>Chitty Chitty Bang Bang</em> at Amazon, and s=
he=E2=80=99ll probably find more stuff to do. But now she=E2=80=99s just
another producer=E2=80=94albeit a really rich one=E2=80=94stripped of the p=
ower and influence that franchise ownership confers.</p><p style=3D"margin:=
0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">You think studios we=
re lining up to make <em>Till</em>, her $25 million <strong>Emmett Till</st=
rong> drama that MGM bankrolled and released in 2022? It grossed just $11 m=
illion worldwide, but Amazon was happy to do it because=E2=80=A6 Bond. Broc=
coli and Wilson have made every industry power list, and there=E2=80=99s ba=
rely an
accolade or commendation they haven=E2=80=99t accepted, including last fall=
=E2=80=99s Thalberg, the Academy=E2=80=99s highest honor. Because=E2=80=A6 =
Bond. And because the Broccolis have stuck to their vision of the character=
 and the franchise=E2=80=94always British, always martinis, always outrageo=
us villains and beautiful <em>femmes fatales</em>. And always <em>their</em=
> final cut. That=E2=80=99s all up to the free shipping people now.=C2=A0</=
p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
